Genotype of animal that includes LOAD1 or LOAD2 terminology LOAD1 = APOE4_HOMOZYGOUS; TREM2R47H_HOMOZYGOUS and LOAD2 = APOE4_HOMOZYGOUS; TREM2R47H_HOMOZYGOUS; ABETA_HOMOZYGOUS. LOAD1 is a mouse strain that has two copies of the APOE4 gene and two copies of the Trem2R47H gene. The APOE4 gene is a risk factor for Alzheimer's disease, and the Trem2R47H gene is a modifier of the risk of Alzheimer's disease. LOAD2 is a mouse strain that has two copies of the APOE4 and Trem2R47H genes, as well as two copies of the Abeta gene. The Abeta gene is a protein that is thought to play a role in the development of Alzheimer's disease. Both LOAD1 and LOAD2 mice are more likely develop Alzheimer's disease at a younger age than mice with other genotypes. This makes the LOAD1 and LOAD2 genotypes valuable tools for studying the development and progression of Alzheimer's disease.

Mean GC content per sample
The median number of genes detected (with nonzero UMI counts) across all cell-associated barcodes
The median number of total Unique Molecular Identifier (UMI) counts across all cell-associated barcodes

Number of PCR cycles to amplify transposased DNA fragments
Ratio of absorbance at 230 nm and 260 nm. Measures protein or other contaminants. Range up to approximately 2.2.
Measure of DNA vs. RNA purity. Range up to approximately 2.0.
The length of the read
The strand from which the read originates in a strand-specific protocol
Valid Values: forward, reverse

Description: RNA Integrity Number

Valid Values: singleEnd, pairedEnd

Description: The nucleotide sequence of the sample barcode used to identify cells from a single sample in cell hashing or multiplexing assays.
Total number of sequencing reads from a library
Fraction of reads with cell barcodes that match the whitelist
Percentage of reads as valid Hi-C interactions (QC metric)
